Psychology980o | Perception and Imagination | http://www.courses.fas.harvard.edu/97975 | instructors: Justin Anthony Junge prereq:Science of Living Systems 20 or its predecessors and one foundational course. term:Half course (fall term). W., 4–6. EXAM GROUP:   17 description:Perception is required to have a mind like yours. How does perceiving work? How are streams of sensory input processed into rich and useful models of the world around you? This course will converge on the 5 senses from many informative angles, explaining how perception tracks and shapes reality, then gives rise to imagination. 
